Wrapper changes.

1. run_gatk.py warns and does not run if an annotated VCF and
recalibrated BAM already exist in the archival location (clean the data
directory up before attempting to reprocess a sample).
2. Added option to ignore sample priority if a custom ordering is
desired, e.g. FIFO.
3. Added option to not run a sample if any step has failed previously.

Implemented (very) basic BAM checking functionality.

1. Check that samtools view returns without error before beginning
pipeline (prior to RealignerTargetCreator and DuplicateMetrics).
2. Every file archived is its own command now in order to highlight
where an issue is if archival fails.
3. An exception is raised if we can't get the prepID for a sample in
RunCvgMetrics (instead of continuing function execution and failing
cryptically later).
4. RunCvgMetrics now logs queries executed.
5. Added mistakenly deleted update_contamination_metrics method back to
RunCvgMetrics.
6. Fixed several very minor bugs.
Logging config file added to branch.
Now returns False instead of raising an exception if Avere load data is not found.
Logging config file added to branch.
Removed deprecated GenotypeConcordance task.

Extensive changes.

1. Commented out (temporarily) data deletions.  Suggested to reintroduce
upon further inclusion of error checking to ensure only happens when
intended.
2. Only allow max of 3 alternate alleles in an active window to avoid
GATK bug (and should only go above this in areas of very questionable
quality).
3. Switched java ParallelGCThreads to 1 so as not to invalidate the
resources requested on the cluster.
4. Changed get_productionvcf to get the VCF on the basis of the prepID
instead of pseudo_prepid, as pseudo_prepid is not always set in the
given table and we already query for it.
5. Fixed logic to get the production VCF and ensure it exists. NB. it
doesn't exist if the previous pipeline wasn't actually run on the
sample.
6. Fixed defining the output file names for DP bin splitting.
7. Changed to always retain chromosome MT DP bins (even though they're
not in the defined regions of interest).
8. GenotypeConcordance raises an error message if no production VCF
exists.
9. Fixed bug getting FILTER field in GenotypeConcordance.subset_vcf.
10. UpdateSeqdbMetrics now requires SplitAndSubsetDPBins instead of
CvgBinning.

Further changes to organization of pipeline:

1. Deleted deprecated CopyBam step.
2. Deleted obvious/unnecessary comments.
3. Removed recording commands to self.script in indivudal tasks; moved
it to parent class.
4. Set the number of cores to use for commands in classes to n_cpu
instead of being hardcoded.
5. Added abstract method _run_post_success() in order to perform any
cleanup operations (e.g. deleting a previously needed BAM) only after
setting the task as a success in the database.
6. Removed adding a deprecated AnnoDBID annotation.
7. Moved some variable declarations from __init__ to pre_shell_commands
so as to not have to set them every time the class is instantiated.
8. Implemented tarballing scripts, logs, and .txt in one file, coverage
bins in another, and GQ bins in a third.
9. Ensured obtaining X & Y BED files in the proper order.
10. Removed commit() after updating a QC metric in favor of only
committing at the end to avoid integrity errors if a crash occurs during
this step and it's restarted.
11. Every task sets the user's umask so as to preserve group write
permissions on all created files.
12. sample_name, capture_kit_bed, sample_type, and scratch are now
optional parameters, and are obtained from SeqDB if not specified.

added fastq logging.  alignment step=1

Miscellaneous changes:

1. Archival now attempts to change permissions on only files owned by
the user running the pipeline (otherwise errors are raised).
2. CombineVariants now bgzips and indexes the generated VCF, rather than
handling it in an unrelated method.
3. Rewrote some of the logic/error checking for fix_phased_vcf(),
including getting GATK annotations from the analysisReady VCF directly,
instead of a "deannotated" VCF which is never created in the pipeline.
4. Pipeline is now tolerant of custom capture samples without an X or Y
targets.  Adjusted the rsync command to accommodate this.
5. Fixed obtaining X & Y target BEDs to make sure they're obtained in
the proper order without relying on non-standard MySQL feature.
6. Fixed prerequisites for both RunCvgMetrics and AlignmentMetrics to
PrintReads (BQSR).
